    </worksheet>
    <worksheet name='Recommended Actions'>
      <layout-options>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>1. Improve Product Quality &amp; Descriptions</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Investigate high‑return sub‑categories (e.g., furniture, binders).</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Update product descriptions and images to reduce mismatches.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Work with suppliers to address quality issues.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>2. Address Return‑Prone Customers</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify customers with consistently high return rates.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Offer personalized support or guidance before purchase.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Consider limiting “trial‑like” purchasing behavior.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>3. Fix Geographic Problem Areas</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Review shipping processes in high‑return states.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Audit packaging quality for long‑distance deliveries.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Adjust inventory placement to reduce transit damage.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>4. Manage Seasonal Spikes</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Prepare for higher returns after major sales periods.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improve customer communication during peak seasons.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Offer clearer expectations on delivery times and product fit.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>5. Resolve Operational Issues</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Reduce shipping errors through better order verification.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improve packaging for fragile or bulky items.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Track supplier‑level return rates and renegotiate terms.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>6. Use the Dashboard for Ongoing Monitoring</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Filter by category, state, and customer segment weekly.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Investigate outliers immediately.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Share insights with operations, logistics, and merchandising teams.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
